The paper focuses on investigating the limitations of likelihood-based generative models for robust classification, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks as the primary tool for experimentation, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
